article.headline: Texas-Arlington 67, Stephen F.Austin 52
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- Brandon Long scored 17 points and three other players had double digits in Texas-Arlington's 67-52 victory over Stephen F. Austin on Wednesday night. Anthony Vereen added 15, Roge'r Guignard scored 12, four from 3-pointers, and Marquez Haynes contributed 11 for the Mavericks (10-7, 3-1 Southland Conference). Tommy Moffitt led Texas-Arlington in rebounding with 10 boards. Eric Bell led with 13 points for the Lumberjacks (11-5, 3-1) while Josh Alexander and Nick Shaw each scored 10 points. Stephen F. Austin was down by only one at the half with the Mavericks leading 30-29. But Texas-Arlington went on a 25-8 scoring run to start the second half and coasted the rest of the way. Long scored 13 points during the run.
